I get the impression from some of these responses that you folks would prefer:<p><pre><code>    struct foo *bar = (struct foo*)malloc(sizeof(struct foo));
</code></pre>
Over:<p><pre><code>    struct foo *bar = malloc(sizeof(*bar));
</code></pre>
I suppose the former is more clear by somebody&#x27;s definition but I am going to continue to consider it somewhat ridiculous.
